<HEADLINE>
<P>
PAPERBACKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES SOLOMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 PACIFIC WAR DIARY by James F. Fahey, edited by Von Hardesty (University of 
Washington Press: $29; 193 pp.) . James Fahey (1918-1991) served on the light 
cruiser U.S.S. Montpelier, engaging the Japanese off the Solomons, the 
Marianas, the Philippines, Okinawa, Borneo and China. Initially published in 
1963, his journal offers a typical bluejacket's view of the war. The most 
moving chapters recount the devastation Fahey witnessed at Hiroshima and the 
rest of Japan immediately in 1945. This illustrated abridgment takes on a 
renewed topicality as the 50th anniversary of the end of the War in the Pacific 
approaches. 
</P>
</TEXT>
