<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANIMALS CROWD RUNWAYS, AIRLINE CANCELS FLIGHTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Air Namibia, the national airline, is canceling flights to rural areas for 
technical reasons: Cows, goats and villagers are crowding the runways. 
</P>
<P>
 The airline on Friday declared one rural airport unsafe for landing. A 
decision is pending about two others, including the former South African air 
base at Ondangwa, the only airport in the north of the southwest African 
nation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
