BRIEFLY: MILITARY: CEREMONY TO HONOR U.S. PILOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Erik Scott Mounsey, the U.S. pilot who died when his Blackhawk helicopter was 
shot down by friendly fire over the Persian Gulf in April, will be honored 
Friday in a ceremony in Culver City. 
</P>
<P>
 The ceremony, scheduled for 11 a.m. at Culver City Park, will include a 
tree-planting and the dedication of a plaque. The Culver City resident is 
survived by his wife, Kaye, and their 2-year-old daughter. 
</P>
