<HEADLINE>
<P>
GM PICKUPS: MUCH ADO ABOUT NOTHING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 "Government Takes Aim at GM Pickups" (Oct. 18) is a further demonstration of 
the Clinton Administration's endless ability to waste energy (taxpayers' 
dollars) on minuscule problems.In Transportation Secretary Federico Pena's 
current attack on side-mounted gas tanks on GMC pickups, his stated numbers are 
15 years and 150 deaths. That averages out to perhaps 10 deaths per year. 
</P>
<P>
 Since 50,000 people die in traffic accidents every year, Secretary Pena, how 
about taking a somewhat larger bite of the apple? 
</P>
<P>
 FRANK A. ANDERSON 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine 
</P>
</TEXT>
