<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: MID-CITY: WESTLAKE; COMMUNITY TO HEAR REDEVELOPMENT PLAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Los Angeles Department of City Planning has invited local residents, 
property and business owners to an open house Wednesday on proposed changes to 
the Westlake community redevelopment plan.  
</P>
<P>
 Amendments to the plan, adopted by the city in 1974, are being considered 
because the area is now one of the city's most densely populated. 
</P>
<P>
 They involve down-zoning some of Westlake's residential areas to relieve 
population density, said Jim Tokunaga, a planning associate with the 
department. 
</P>
<P>
 Draft documents on the proposed changes will be available to the public, and 
presentations will be made by city staff at 5 and 7 p.m.  
</P>
<P>
 Staff will also be available to answer questions and listen to recommendations 
from the community. 
</P>
<P>
 The meeting will be held from 4 to 8 p.m. in the multipurpose room of 
Esperanza Elementary School, 689 Little St. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 485-3180. 
</P>
</TEXT>
