<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTHEAST: SOUTH GATE; VOLUNTEERS TO STAFF POLICE DROP-IN SITE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SIMON ROMERO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city will open a police drop-in center next week at Montara Avenue 
Elementary School that will serve as a convenient, comfortable place for 
residents to bring concerns and obtain information about law enforcement and 
safety. 
</P>
<P>
 "This unique center will mean that the police and the city will be that much 
closer to the pulse of the community and thus better able to serve the 
community," said Mayor Albert T. Robles. 
</P>
<P>
 The center will open Nov. 15 and will be staffed by civilian volunteers who 
live in the neighborhood surrounding the school at 11018 Montara Ave. Residents 
will be able to get information on home and traffic safety, gang and drug 
prevention, and city services Tuesdays and Thursdays from 2 to 4 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 "We consider this a pilot program and look forward to having a similar program 
established in each of our schools throughout the city," Robles said. 
</P>
<P>
 The project is part of the city's community-based policing efforts, which aim 
to develop better relations between the community and police. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 563-9565. SIMON ROMERO 
</P>
</TEXT>
