<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTHWEST: CRENSHAW; CENTER TO HOLD PARENTING WORKSHOP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Natural Way Educational Center is sponsoring a workshop Saturday designed 
to improve parenting techniques. 
</P>
<P>
 The workshop will examine a variety of parental issues, including parent/child 
relationship building, discipline techniques, community support networks and 
ways to help children cope with grief. 
</P>
<P>
 The workshop, which will include refreshments and sessions for children ages 5 
and older, will be from 9:30 a.m. to 1:30 p.m. at St. Paul's Presbyterian 
Church annex, 5100 Coliseum St. 
</P>
<P>
 Workshops will also be held Nov. 12 and Dec. 10 at the same location. 
</P>
<P>
 The Natural Way Education Center is a Los Angeles-based nonprofit group 
dedicated to increasing the skills of African American parents. The cost of the 
workshop is $50, but the fee will be waived for those who cannot afford it. 
</P>
<P>
 Information and registration: (213) 936-8063. 
</P>
</TEXT>
