<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; VISTA TO CHANGE SOME ROUTES, SERVICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Four months after launching a new countywide bus program, the Ventura County 
Transportation Commission has agreed to tinker with the service to better meet 
the needs of commuters. 
</P>
<P>
 Beginning Nov. 14, service on the Ventura Intercity Service Transit Authority, 
or VISTA, will stop at Oak Park High School four times a day. 
</P>
<P>
 The Oak Park service will be added to the East line, which also stops in 
Thousand Oaks, Simi Valley and Moorpark. 
</P>
<P>
 Buses on the Central line, which travels between Oxnard and Camarillo, will 
begin stopping at Oxnard Airport. 
</P>
<P>
 And a stop at Lewis Road in Camarillo will be added to the VISTA-101 route, 
which travels from Ventura to Thousand Oaks along the Ventura Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
 The commission on Friday also agreed to reduce midday service on the Central 
and East routes because of low ridership. 
</P>
<P>
 Average daily ridership on the six VISTA routes has more than doubled since 
the program's inception. In July, an average of 413 riders boarded VISTA buses 
each day. In October, the average daily ridership reached 852. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information about VISTA, call the commission's information center at 
1-800-438-1112. SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</TEXT>
