<HEADLINE>
<P>
DEFENSE HELPS OREGON STATE DEFEAT PACIFIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cameron Reynolds, Oregon State's offensive star, credits the Beavers' defense 
for his team's 24-12 victory over Pacific. 
</P>
<P>
 "They played incredible," Reynolds said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Tigers got within Oregon State's 20-yard line six times but had to settle 
for one touchdown and two field goals. 
</P>
<P>
 Reynolds caught a 57-yard touchdown pass from Don Shanklin and scored again on 
a 74-yard run in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
 Oregon State (3-6) overcame three fumbles and 10 penalties for a loss of 80 
yards to end a two-game losing streak. 
</P>
<P>
 The loss is the first in three games for the Tigers (5-4). 
</P>
</TEXT>
