<HEADLINE>
<P>
CLEMENTS SETS KILL RECORD IN CSUN SWEEP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Missy Clements had 22 kills to become Cal State Northridge's all-time leader 
in a 15-4, 15-13, 15-5 sweep of Cal Poly San Luis Obispo in a nonconference 
women's volleyball match Saturday night at Matador Gymnasium. 
</P>
<P>
 Clements, a 5-foot-11 senior outside hitter from La Habra High, needed 18 
kills to break Northridge's career record of 1,326 set by Kathleen Dixon from 
1987-90.After getting 10 kills in the first game, she had eight in the second. 
</P>
<P>
 The match was stopped after Clements' 18th kill, and she received a standing 
ovation from the crowd of 386 and congratulations from her teammates. 
</P>
<P>
 She added four kills in the third game to increase her career total to 1,331 
with two matches left in the regular season. 
</P>
<P>
 The victory was the third in a row for Northridge (15-8) and the fifth in its 
last six matches. 
</P>
<P>
 The Matadors had a .419 hitting percentage, four of six starters posting marks 
of .400 or better. 
</P>
<P>
 Heather Anderson had 12 kills, 14 digs and three blocks for CSUN and Aimee 
Stone added nine kills. 
</P>
</TEXT>
