<P>
MARINERS SAIL TO SECOND VICTORY OVER UTAH, 5-2 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRIS WYKES, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Ventura Mariners defeated the Utah Lightning, 5-2, Saturday night in the 
second contest of a three-game, Western States Hockey League series at the Easy 
Street Arena. 
</P>
<P>
 The Mariners (6-1-1) used first-period goals by WSHL scoring leader Rico 
Fulgenzi, Ace Pascual and David Mischel to pull away from the Lightning 
(0-10-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura won the series opener, 9-6, Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Utah stayed in the game on the 46-save performance of goalie Chad Walsh. 
</P>
<P>
 "We tried to keep the play wide and spread them out," said Mischel, who scored 
what proved to be the game-winning goal on a slap shot from the top of the left 
faceoff circle. "If we use our speed they can't grab us." 
</P>
<P>
 Mariner Coach Sean McGillivray agreed, saying Utah won many of the physical 
battles while playing a conservative game. 
</P>
<P>
 "They were letting us get the puck in close and then jumping on us," he said. 
"They really cleared us out in front of the net." 
</P>
<P>
 The Mariners got third-period goals from Fulgenzi, who has 19 points this 
season, and Steve Petritz. Jordan Leithem had 11 saves. 
</P>
