<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; BELL-JEFF'S WIN MARRED BY FIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOE SCHLOSSER and MIKE GLAZE and STEVE GALLUZZO and MIKE YEAMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In a game marred by more than 250 yards in penalties, two player ejections and 
a postgame brawl that involved players and fans, visiting Bell-Jeff High 
emerged with a 27-7 victory over Cathedral in a Santa Fe League contest 
Saturday afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
 The fight broke out when the teams met to shake hands after the game. 
</P>
<P>
 "There's been bad blood between these two schools for years," said Bell-Jeff 
assistant Brett Woodlief, who was bleeding from the mouth after being hit 
during the melee. "I took two or three punches out there and I hate to say it, 
but I could see this coming from the beginning of the game." 
</P>
<P>
 Richard Szeptycki completed seven of 12 passes for 96 yards and a touchdown 
for Bell-Jeff (5-4, 4-2), which scored 20 points in the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Mary Star 27, St. Genevieve 0 -- Five St. Genevieve players were taken to the 
hospital because of injuries and the second half of the Santa Fe League game at 
Birmingham High was played with a running clock. 
</P>
<P>
 All of the injuries occurred during the second quarter. Quarterback Vince 
Pisano, who injured his shoulder, was taken to a local hospital by his parents, 
as was lineman Mike Hanson (neck). Running back Nelvine Ocampo (concussion), 
running back Ray Cruz (irregular heartbeat) and backup quarterback Rodney 
Villanueva (unspecified chest injury) were transported by ambulance. 
</P>
<P>
 Village Christian 31, Maranatha 0 -- Tony Yousif caught a touchdown pass and 
ran for another to lead the host Crusaders (6-3, 4-0) in an Alpha League game. 
</P>
<P>
 Ignacio Brache kicked a 55-yard field goal. 
</P>
<P>
 Calabasas 40, Santa Clara 13 -- Ken Morris had 134 yards rushing and three 
touchdowns for the Coyotes (3-6, 2-1) in a Frontier League victory over the 
Saints (2-7, 1-3). 
</P>
<P>
 Harvard-Westlake 23, St. Monica 20 -- Abed Abusaleh gained 94 yards in 28 
carries and scored three touchdowns as the Wolverines clinched the Camino Real 
League championship Friday night at Santa Monica College. JOE SCHLOSSER and 
MIKE GLAZE and STEVE GALLUZZO and MIKE YEAMAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
