<HEADLINE>
<P>
AUCTION MARKS ANNIVERSARY OF LOS ANGELES CONSERVANCY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Los Angeles Conservancy will celebrate its 16th anniversary with a buffet 
dinner and auction on Nov. 19, from 7 to 11 p.m., in the downtown Central 
Library, which the Conservancy was formed to save. 
</P>
<P>
 The Conservancy also helped preserve Bullocks Wilshire and the Wiltern 
Theatre.The nonprofit organization regularly holds downtown L.A. walking tours 
and "The Last Remaining Seats," a showcase of classic movies in landmark movie 
palaces. 
</P>
<P>
 Among the items to be auctioned are Julius Shulman photos of the Central 
Library; a night for two in the master suite of the Gamble House; weekend trips 
to historic destinations; special tours of historic Los Angeles, and 
one-of-a-kind bookends designed for the anniversary by more than two dozen 
architects and artists. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets, at $75 each, may be purchased through the Conservancy at 727 W. 7th 
St., Suite 955, Los Angeles 90017. For more information, phone (213) 623-CITY. 
</P>
