<HEADLINE>
<P>
PIT BULL KILLED BABY ABANDONED IN POMONA BACK YARD, AUTHORITIES SAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A newborn baby boy whose mutilated body was found in the back yard of a Pomona 
home was apparently mauled to death by a pit bull dog kept in the yard, police 
said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Pomona police had speculated earlier that the infant was killed elsewhere 
before being dumped Friday near a rusting car in the littered yard of a 
working-class neighborhood home. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents of Orange Grove Avenue discovered the body Friday afternoon. Police 
said the body showed evidence of head injuries as well as severed testicles and 
a missing arm. 
</P>
<P>
 But an autopsy Saturday indicated that the infant died "as a result of trauma 
caused by multiple dog bites," Police Sgt. Jeff Anderson said. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities say the infant is possibly Latino. They have requested help from 
the public in identifying him. 
</P>
</TEXT>
