<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WRONG BIRD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Re: "Nature's Open House" (Oct. 30): (You) did an excellent job of reporting 
on the open house at Audubon's Starr Ranch.However, (you) did err in describing 
the birds in the sanctuary. Any birder knows there are no blue jays in the 
sanctuary as reported. True, there are jays there that are blue, but blue jays 
they're not. They are scrub jays. The bird called the blue jay is an eastern 
bird not found west of the Rocky Mountains. 
</P>
<P>
 JAMES R. GALLAGHER 
