<HEADLINE>
<P>
IT'S TREES, PLEASE, IN LAGUNA BEACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 What has made Laguna unique down through the years are: first, the people who 
created this delightful place; and second, the trees. 
</P>
<P>
 The founders laid the town out beautifully with Heisler Park and lovely 
vistas. 
</P>
<P>
 In the '70s, people gave us our lively Main Beach "window to the sea" and 
Pines Park and a mandate for a small town with no large hotels. 
</P>
<P>
 But in last analyses, the great-granddaddy of gifts is our natural greenbelt 
as the ultimate barrier to Los Angeles, which is knocking at our door eager to 
gobble us up! 
</P>
<P>
 So when you choose your favorite candidates, first and foremost be sure of his 
and her commitment to our (natural) greenbelt. 
</P>
<P>
 GENE ATHERTON 
</P>
