<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE INVESTIGATING LAGUNA BEACH BEATING AS A HATE CRIME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE MARQUIS, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two assailants attacked a man in broad daylight Saturday, hurling anti-gay 
epithets and beating him, apparently in a dispute over money that police are 
investigating as a hate crime, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Donald Nichols, 18, of Laguna Beach and a 16-year-old suspect were arrested 
later in the day on suspicion of robbery and assault with a deadly weapon, 
Detective Jason Kravetz said. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim, identified only as a Laguna Beach man in his 30s, was approached 
from behind about 1:30 p.m. while he walking south on the sidewalk in the 700 
block of Coast Highway, Kravetz said. Nichols pulled the man to the ground, 
then was joined in the assault by the 16-year-old who kicked the victim in the 
head, Kravetz said. 
</P>
<P>
 Kravetz said the victim and witnesses reported that the assailants yelled 
anti-gay epithets during the beating, which went on for several minutes. He 
said the suspects and victim knew each other and apparently were engaged in a 
dispute over money. The assailants robbed the victim, but Kravetz would not say 
how much money was taken. 
</P>
<P>
 A man who witnessed the attack then came out of a nearby business and 
threatened to call the police, Kravetz said. The suspects fled in a Honda that 
was parked nearby. 
</P>
<P>
 A woman who witnessed the attack told police she recognized Nichols as someone 
with whom she had attended Laguna Beach High School, Kravetz said. Nichols was 
arrested at his home about two hours later. 
</P>
<P>
 The 16-year-old, a Laguna Beach High School student, was arrested about 7:30 
Saturday night as he was driving on Coast Highway near the site of the attack, 
Kravetz said. 
</P>
<P>
 Kravetz said police will recommend to the district attorney's office that the 
assault be prosecuted as a hate crime. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim suffered cuts and bruises but declined medical attention, the 
detective said. 
</P>
<P>
 The attack was the second recent one in Laguna Beach that police investigated 
as a hate crime. In September, two tourists from Salt Lake City were attacked 
and robbed while walking on a stretch of beach. Police said the assailants 
uttered an anti-gay slur during the attack and shots were fired. 
</P>
<P>
 Those attackers were never found, but police said the two attacks do not 
appear to be related. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA110694-0386 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 096156 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
November 6, 1994, Sunday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
