<HEADLINE>
<P>
GARDEN GROVE APARTMENT FIRE DISPLACES 16 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sixteen people from three families had to be evacuated Friday from their 
apartment building after a fire broke out in a carport and caused extensive 
damage to three units, authorities and a Red Cross official said. 
</P>
<P>
 The blaze broke out about 8:30 p.m. in a carport at 11062 Cynthia Circle at 
the Pepper Tree Apartments, Garden Grove fire officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 A Red Cross official said the agency put a family of six adults up in a motel 
over the weekend because their apartment had sustained heavy smoke damage. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's not inhabitable at this point," said Scott Tokar, a volunteer public 
information officer for the Orange County chapter of the Red Cross. 
</P>
<P>
 The other 10 people displaced by the fire made their own arrangements for 
emergency shelter, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities released no other information about the fire. 
</P>
</TEXT>
