<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; LANCERS ROLL PAST BRETHREN CHRISTIAN, 28-7 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JASON HILL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Orange Lutheran rushed for 293 yards and four touchdowns to defeat Brethren 
Christian, 28-7, in an Olympic League game Saturday night at Artesia High 
School. 
</P>
<P>
 The Lancers (7-2, 3-1 in league), who will play at undefeated Valley Christian 
on Friday for the league championship, scored on their first possession when 
Matt Stratton ran in from 32 yards to give Orange Lutheran a 7-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Tim Smith's interception on the opening play of the second quarter gave the 
Lancers the ball on Brethren Christian's 26-yard line. Six plays later, running 
back Che Holloway scored on a two-yard dive. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Lutheran took a 21-0 third-quarter lead when quarterback Joe Juliano 
kept the option and ran seven yards into the end zone. 
</P>
<P>
 On fourth and two, Brethren Christian (1-8, 0-4) scored when quarterback Ryan 
Babcock ran 63 yards for a touchdown to cut Orange Lutheran's lead to 21-7. 
</P>
<P>
 The Lancers bounced back with an eight-play scoring drive capped by Stratton's 
second touchdown, a 24-yard run. 
</P>
<P>
 The Warriors had one last opportunity to score, driving to Orange Lutheran's 
seven-yard line, but Smith intercepted Babcock in the end zone with 3:54 left 
to play. JASON HILL 
</P>
</TEXT>
