<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOOTBALL ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By COREY LYONS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In an Arrowhead League game: 
</P>
<P>
 Southern California Christian 20, Hesperia Christian 19 -- Southern California 
Christian scored its first points of the regular season and produced a 
fourth-quarter comeback to edge Hesperia Christian. 
</P>
<P>
 The Flames (2-7, 1-3), who were shut out in their first three league games, 
won when quarterback Steve Schinofen hit Jeremy Smith in the left corner of the 
end zone for a two-point conversion.On the previous play, running back Laramie 
Lumley barged in from five yards to pull the Flames to within 19-18 with five 
minutes 29 seconds remaining.  
</P>
<P>
 Despite completing only one pass in the game, the Patriots (1-8, 0-4) scored 
on three consecutive touchdowns in the second half to take the lead, after 
trailing, 12-0, at halftime. Leading, 13-12, early in the fourth quarter, 
senior tailback Tom Thompson fought off several Flame tacklers for an 80-yard 
touchdown run and 19-12 Patriot lead immediately after a Flame missed 
field-goal attempt. 
</P>
<P>
 Thompson finished with 143 rushing yards in 11 carries. COREY LYONS 
</P>
</TEXT>
