<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; USC'S HANSEN ADVANCES TO REGIONAL TENNIS FINAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JASON REID 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 USC's Brett Hansen, formerly of UC Irvine and Newport Harbor High, beat 
top-seeded Robert Janecek of UCLA to advance to the final of the ITA Southern 
California Men's Tennis Regional on Saturday at UCI. 
</P>
<P>
 Hansen won, 6-3, 7-6, and will face Roger Pettersson of Nevada Las Vegas at 
10:30 a.m. today.Pettersson beat Irvine's Marc-Andre Tardif, 7-6, 6-1, in 
Saturday's other semifinal. 
</P>
<P>
 Tardif also lost in doubles. He and Chris Tontz fell to Simon Aspelin and Troy 
Budgen of Pepperdine, 6-7, 6-4, 6-4, in the quarterfinals. Aspelin and Budgen 
will play Chris Hill and Mike Jessup, also of Pepperdine, in today's final at 
noon. 
</P>
<P>
 In men's exhibition basketball: 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach State 102, High Five America 94 -- Long Beach State managed the 
victory despite committing 35 turnovers in front of 1,557 at The Gold Mine. 
</P>
<P>
 Sophomore guard James Cotton scored a team-high 18 points and forward Jeff 
Clifton had 35 for High Five America. Cotton also had seven rebounds for the 
49ers, who led by as many as 18 points (37-19) in the first half and were 
ahead, 48-36, at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
 High Five America Coach Rle Nichols was ejected with 4:07 to play after 
receiving his second technical. High Five America guard Rod Hannibal, who 
completed his eligibility at Long Beach last season, was ejected with 1:12 
remaining after he pushed junior center Brian Yankelevitz. Hannibal scored 14 
points. JASON REID 
</P>
</TEXT>
