<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In the Orange Empire Conference water polo championships: 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Coast takes second -- James Giulianotti scored five goals to lead 
Grossmont past Orange Coast, 15-7, Saturday in the Orange Empire Conference 
water polo championships. Grossmont jumped to an 8-3 halftime lead that the 
Pirates were unable to overcome. 
</P>
<P>
 Giulianotti's brother, John, added four goals for Grossmont. Shad Wicker led 
Orange Coast with three goals as the Pirates finished in second place. 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Santiago took third place with an 8-4 victory over Saddleback. The Dons 
scored six second-half goals for the victory. 
</P>
<P>
 John Gniffke scored three goals for Rancho Santiago and teammate Jay Rosales 
added two. 
</P>
<P>
 In other games: 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress 11, Palomar 9 -- Mustafa Hassan had four goals and Kevin Hearn had two 
for Cypress in the consolation game. In an earlier game, Cypress was defeated 
by San Diego Mesa, 13-8. 
</P>
<P>
 In the final of the South Coast tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Golden West 11, Long Beach 6 -- Matt Braun scored four goals and John Chomin 
added three as Golden West, ranked second in the state, beat No. 1 Long Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 Jason Stanton had 14 saves for Golden West (25-2). Long Beach is 18-4-1. 
</P>
